      "side": 1,
      "message": "Strictly speaking, commit can be requested from Git server w/o knowing which ref commit belongs to:\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/a/30701724\n\nGiven default \"git clone\" sets refs/heads/*, it\u0027s quite common (and that\u0027s what bot_update pretty much does) to fetch\n$ git fetch # default refspec of refs/heads/*:refs/heads/*\nthen locally expect commit to already be known:\n$ git checkout $REVISION\n\nSo, I think refs/heads/master is not a really a good default if no ref is specified .\n\nHowever, we should encourage ref to be set if known, promising faster fetching times some day...",
